51// Utility struct for grabbing metadata from a VideoFrame and processing it
52// asynchronously without needing the actual frame data.
53// Additionally the caller can bundle information from the current clock
54// when the metadata is captured, for accurate reporting and not needeing
55// multiple calls to clock->Now().
56struct VideoFrameMetaData {
57 VideoFrameMetaData(const webrtc::VideoFrame& frame, Timestamp now)
58 : rtp_timestamp(frame.timestamp()),
59 timestamp_us(frame.timestamp_us()),
60 ntp_time_ms(frame.ntp_time_ms()),
61 width(frame.width()),
62 height(frame.height()),
63 decode_timestamp(now) {}
64
65 int64_t render_time_ms() const {
66 return timestamp_us / rtc::kNumMicrosecsPerMillisec;
67 }
68
69 const uint32_t rtp_timestamp;
70 const int64_t timestamp_us;
71 const int64_t ntp_time_ms;
72 const int width;
73 const int height;
74
75 const Timestamp decode_timestamp;
76};
77
78class VideoReceiveStream2 : public webrtc::VideoReceiveStream,
79 public rtc::VideoSinkInterface<VideoFrame>,
80 public NackSender,
81 public OnCompleteFrameCallback,
82 public Syncable,
83 public CallStatsObserver {
84 public:
85 // The default number of milliseconds to pass before re-requesting a key frame
86 // to be sent.
87 static constexpr int kMaxWaitForKeyFrameMs = 200;
88 // The maximum number of buffered encoded frames when encoded output is
89 // configured.
90 static constexpr size_t kBufferedEncodedFramesMaxSize = 60;
91
92 VideoReceiveStream2(TaskQueueFactory* task_queue_factory,
93 TaskQueueBase* current_queue,
94 RtpStreamReceiverControllerInterface* receiver_controller,
95 int num_cpu_cores,
96 PacketRouter* packet_router,
97 VideoReceiveStream::Config config,
98 ProcessThread* process_thread,
99 CallStats* call_stats,
100 Clock* clock,
101 VCMTiming* timing);
102 ~VideoReceiveStream2() override;
103
104 const Config& config() const { return config_; }
105
106 void SignalNetworkState(NetworkState state);
107 bool DeliverRtcp(const uint8_t* packet, size_t length);
108
109 void SetSync(Syncable* audio_syncable);
110
111 // Implements webrtc::VideoReceiveStream.
112 void Start() override;
113 void Stop() override;
114
115 webrtc::VideoReceiveStream::Stats GetStats() const override;
116
117 // SetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs and GetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs are called
118 // from webrtc/api level and requested by user code. For e.g. blink/js layer
119 // in Chromium.
120 bool SetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs(int delay_ms) override;
121 int GetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs() const override;
122
123 void SetFrameDecryptor(
124 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameDecryptorInterface> frame_decryptor) override;
125 void SetDepacketizerToDecoderFrameTransformer(
126 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer) override;
127
128 // Implements rtc::VideoSinkInterface<VideoFrame>.
129 void OnFrame(const VideoFrame& video_frame) override;
130
131 // Implements NackSender.
132 // For this particular override of the interface,
133 // only (buffering_allowed == true) is acceptable.
134 void SendNack(const std::vector<uint16_t>& sequence_numbers,
135 bool buffering_allowed) override;
136
137 // Implements OnCompleteFrameCallback.
138 void OnCompleteFrame(std::unique_ptr<EncodedFrame> frame) override;
139
140 // Implements CallStatsObserver::OnRttUpdate
141 void OnRttUpdate(int64_t avg_rtt_ms, int64_t max_rtt_ms) override;
142
143 // Implements Syncable.
144 uint32_t id() const override;
145 absl::optional<Syncable::Info> GetInfo() const override;
146 bool GetPlayoutRtpTimestamp(uint32_t* rtp_timestamp,
147 int64_t* time_ms) const override;
148 void SetEstimatedPlayoutNtpTimestampMs(int64_t ntp_timestamp_ms,
149 int64_t time_ms) override;
150
151 // SetMinimumPlayoutDelay is only called by A/V sync.
152 bool SetMinimumPlayoutDelay(int delay_ms) override;
153
154 std::vector<webrtc::RtpSource> GetSources() const override;
155
156 RecordingState SetAndGetRecordingState(RecordingState state,
157 bool generate_key_frame) override;
158 void GenerateKeyFrame() override;
159
160 private:
161 void CreateAndRegisterExternalDecoder(const Decoder& decoder);
162 int64_t GetMaxWaitMs() const RTC_RUN_ON(decode_queue_);
163 void StartNextDecode() RTC_RUN_ON(decode_queue_);
164 void HandleEncodedFrame(std::unique_ptr<EncodedFrame> frame)
165 RTC_RUN_ON(decode_queue_);
166 void HandleFrameBufferTimeout(int64_t now_ms, int64_t wait_ms)
167 RTC_RUN_ON(worker_sequence_checker_);
168 void UpdatePlayoutDelays() const
169 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(worker_sequence_checker_);
170 void RequestKeyFrame(int64_t timestamp_ms)
171 RTC_RUN_ON(worker_sequence_checker_);
172 void HandleKeyFrameGeneration(bool received_frame_is_keyframe,
173 int64_t now_ms,
174 bool always_request_key_frame,
175 bool keyframe_request_is_due)
176 RTC_RUN_ON(worker_sequence_checker_);
177 bool IsReceivingKeyFrame(int64_t timestamp_ms) const
178 RTC_RUN_ON(worker_sequence_checker_);
179 int DecodeAndMaybeDispatchEncodedFrame(std::unique_ptr<EncodedFrame> frame)
180 RTC_RUN_ON(decode_queue_);
181
182 void UpdateHistograms();
183
184 RTC_NO_UNIQUE_ADDRESS SequenceChecker worker_sequence_checker_;
185 RTC_NO_UNIQUE_ADDRESS SequenceChecker module_process_sequence_checker_;
186
187 TaskQueueFactory* const task_queue_factory_;
188
189 TransportAdapter transport_adapter_;
190 const VideoReceiveStream::Config config_;
191 const int num_cpu_cores_;
192 TaskQueueBase* const worker_thread_;
193 Clock* const clock_;
194
195 CallStats* const call_stats_;
196
197 bool decoder_running_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_sequence_checker_) = false;
198 bool decoder_stopped_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(decode_queue_) = true;
199
200 SourceTracker source_tracker_;
201 ReceiveStatisticsProxy stats_proxy_;
202 // Shared by media and rtx stream receivers, since the latter has no RtpRtcp
203 // module of its own.
204 const std::unique_ptr<ReceiveStatistics> rtp_receive_statistics_;
205
206 std::unique_ptr<VCMTiming> timing_; // Jitter buffer experiment.
207 VideoReceiver2 video_receiver_;
208 std::unique_ptr<rtc::VideoSinkInterface<VideoFrame>> incoming_video_stream_;
209 RtpVideoStreamReceiver2 rtp_video_stream_receiver_;
210 std::unique_ptr<VideoStreamDecoder> video_stream_decoder_;
211 RtpStreamsSynchronizer rtp_stream_sync_;
212
213 // TODO(nisse, philipel): Creation and ownership of video encoders should be
214 // moved to the new VideoStreamDecoder.
215 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<VideoDecoder>> video_decoders_;
216
217 // Members for the new jitter buffer experiment.
218 std::unique_ptr<video_coding::FrameBuffer> frame_buffer_;
219
220 std::unique_ptr<RtpStreamReceiverInterface> media_receiver_;
221 std::unique_ptr<RtxReceiveStream> rtx_receive_stream_;
222 std::unique_ptr<RtpStreamReceiverInterface> rtx_receiver_;
223
224 // Whenever we are in an undecodable state (stream has just started or due to
225 // a decoding error) we require a keyframe to restart the stream.
226 bool keyframe_required_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(decode_queue_) = true;
227
228 // If we have successfully decoded any frame.
229 bool frame_decoded_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(decode_queue_) = false;
230
231 int64_t last_keyframe_request_ms_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(decode_queue_) = 0;
232 int64_t last_complete_frame_time_ms_
233 RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_sequence_checker_) = 0;
234
235 // Keyframe request intervals are configurable through field trials.
236 const int max_wait_for_keyframe_ms_;
237 const int max_wait_for_frame_ms_;
238
239 // All of them tries to change current min_playout_delay on |timing_| but
240 // source of the change request is different in each case. Among them the
241 // biggest delay is used. -1 means use default value from the |timing_|.
242 //
243 // Minimum delay as decided by the RTP playout delay extension.
244 int frame_minimum_playout_delay_ms_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_sequence_checker_) =
245 -1;
246 // Minimum delay as decided by the setLatency function in "webrtc/api".
247 int base_minimum_playout_delay_ms_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_sequence_checker_) =
248 -1;
249 // Minimum delay as decided by the A/V synchronization feature.
250 int syncable_minimum_playout_delay_ms_
251 RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_sequence_checker_) = -1;
252
253 // Maximum delay as decided by the RTP playout delay extension.
254 int frame_maximum_playout_delay_ms_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_sequence_checker_) =
255 -1;
256
257 // Function that is triggered with encoded frames, if not empty.
258 std::function<void(const RecordableEncodedFrame&)>
259 encoded_frame_buffer_function_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(decode_queue_);
260 // Set to true while we're requesting keyframes but not yet received one.
261 bool keyframe_generation_requested_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_sequence_checker_) =
262 false;
263 // Lock to avoid unnecessary per-frame idle wakeups in the code.
264 webrtc::Mutex pending_resolution_mutex_;
265 // Signal from decode queue to OnFrame callback to fill pending_resolution_.
266 // absl::nullopt - no resolution needed. 0x0 - next OnFrame to fill with
267 // received resolution. Not 0x0 - OnFrame has filled a resolution.
268 absl::optional<RecordableEncodedFrame::EncodedResolution> pending_resolution_
269 RTC_GUARDED_BY(pending_resolution_mutex_);
270 // Buffered encoded frames held while waiting for decoded resolution.
271 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<EncodedFrame>> buffered_encoded_frames_
272 RTC_GUARDED_BY(decode_queue_);
273
274 // Set by the field trial WebRTC-LowLatencyRenderer. The parameter |enabled|
275 // determines if the low-latency renderer algorithm should be used for the
276 // case min playout delay=0 and max playout delay>0.
277 FieldTrialParameter<bool> low_latency_renderer_enabled_;
278 // Set by the field trial WebRTC-LowLatencyRenderer. The parameter
279 // |include_predecode_buffer| determines if the predecode buffer should be
280 // taken into account when calculating maximum number of frames in composition
281 // queue.
282 FieldTrialParameter<bool> low_latency_renderer_include_predecode_buffer_;
283
284 // Set by the field trial WebRTC-PreStreamDecoders. The parameter |max|
285 // determines the maximum number of decoders that are created up front before
286 // any video frame has been received.
287 FieldTrialParameter<int> maximum_pre_stream_decoders_;
288
289 // Defined last so they are destroyed before all other members.
290 rtc::TaskQueue decode_queue_;
291
292 // Used to signal destruction to potentially pending tasks.
293 ScopedTaskSafety task_safety_;
294};
295} // namespace internal
296} // namespace webrtc
